ablished at the time of the Reformation, although  <b>Nicolas</b>  is still occasionally found.  St Nicholas  was a 4th-century bishop of Myra in Lycia, about whom virtually nothing factual is known, although a vast body of legend grew up around him, and he became the patron saint of Greece and of Russia, as well as of children, sailors, merchants, and pawnbrokers. His feast day is  6 December , and among the many roles which legend has assigned to him is that of bringer of Christmas presents, in the guise of ‘Santa Claus’ (an alteration of the Dutch form of his name, <i>Sinterklaas</i>)."],"variants":[{"name":"Nickolas","meanings":["Mainly U.S.: variant spelling of   Nicholas  , influenced by the short form   Nick ."]},{"name":"Nicolas","meanings":["From Late Greek.  See  <b>Nicholas</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Nicholas de Morton was born in 1195, in England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 daughter with Agnes. He died in 1259, in his hometown, at the age of 64."},"et":{"1195–1259":"1195–1259","1212–1291":"1212–1291","1248–1291":"1248–1291","1248":"1248","1259":"1259","1212":"1212","1195":"1195","1291":"1291","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Church Gresley, Derbyshire, England":"Church Gresley, Derbyshire, England"},"fi":{"1195–1259":"1195–1259","1212–1291":"1212–1291","1248–1291":"1248–1291","1248":"1248","1259":"1259","1212":"1212","1195":"1195","1291":"1291","England, United Kingdom":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Church Gresley, Derbyshire, England":"Church Gresley, Derbyshire, England"},"fr":{"1195–1259":"1195–1259","1212–1291":"1212–1291","1248–1291":"1248–1291","1248":"1248","1259":"1259","1212":"1212","1195":"1195","1291":"1291","England, United Kingdom":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Church Gresley, Derbyshire, England":"Church Gresley, Derbyshire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Nicholas de Morton est né en 1195, à Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Il a eu au moins 1 fille avec Agnes. Il est décédé en 1259, dans sa ville natale, à l’âge de 64 